www.thejoyofeating.com/products.asp?catagory=SWEETS&subcatagory=Cakes',NULL),(26518,NULL,1135,2778,'Sara Lee produces sweets that are high in added sugars','http://www.thejoyofeating.com/products.asp?catagory=SWEETS&subcatagory=Cakes',NULL),(26517,NULL,1135,2776,'No Deviation',NULL,NULL),(26516,NULL,1135,2773,'Sara Lee pled guilty to two misdemeanor counts in connection with a listeriosis outbreak that led to the deaths of at least 21 consumers who ate Ball Park Franks hot dogs and other meat products. One hundred people were seriously injured. The company paid a $200,000 fine. In 2005, and 2007 Sara Lee issued recalls for products that may have contained metal fragments, undeclared milk products and potential listeria contamination.  ','http://google2.fda.gov/search?q=sara+lee+inc&x=0&y=0&client=FDAgov&proxystylesheet=FDAgov&output=xml_no_dtd&sort=date%253AD%253AL%253Ad1&site=FDAgov-Recalls-Safety: http://www.knowmore.org/wiki/index.php?title=Ball_Park_Franks_Fiasco:_21_Dead%2C_%24200%2C000_Fine',NULL),(26513,NULL,1135,2763,'No Deviation',NULL,NULL),(26514,NULL,1135,2766,'No Deviation',NULL,NULL),(26515,NULL,1135,2769,'On several Sara Lee web sites, the company muses about how consumers are likely to mistakenly believe that many “whole grain” breads are actually more like whole wheat bread than white bread, and chides its competitors for not being “100-percent whole-grain.” Yet Sara Lee helps foster that confusion by marketing a “Soft & Smooth Made with Whole Grain White Bread” and falsely claiming that it is as nutritious as whole wheat bread. Today the nonprofit Center for Science in the Public Interest served the company with formal notice that it will file suit against the company if the misleading claims continue. ','http://www.cspinet.org/new/200712171_print.html',NULL),(26512,NULL,1135,2758,'The American Federation of State, County and Municipal Employees (AFSCME), which controls 8,424 Sara Lee shares wants the corporation to allow shareholders input on issues of executive pay. Although stocks fell, CEO Brenda Barnes’s salary rose from $883,333 in 2004 to $1 million in 2005. Her bonuses rose from $425,392 in 2004 to $1.14 million in 2005. The AFSCME proposal calls for shareholders to vote and approve the “Compensation Discussion and Analysis” section of the proxy each year.','http://www.knowmore.org/wiki/index.php?title=Sara_Lee_Corp.',NULL),(36965,NULL,1615,3058,'Mistic comes packaged in a glass recyclable bottle.',NULL,NULL),(36966,NULL,1615,3041,'Beginning in May, Mistic will extend its \"Go Bold\" campaign, via Deutsch, New York. New print continues to show characters with glowing eyes that have been \"electrified\" by the taste of the drink. It will run in publications such as FHM, Glamour and Spin. Radio spots will support the 16 oz. core line-up as well as new carafes with new, more contemporary labels designed by FutureBrand Coleman, New York, due this spring. \n','www.allbusiness.com/marketing-advertising/branding-brand-development/4679735-1.html',NULL),(26511,NULL,1135,2755,'Sara Lee pled guilty to two misdemeanor counts in connection with a listeriosis outbreak that led to the deaths of at least 21 consumers who ate Ball Park Franks hot dogs and other meat products. One hundred people were seriously injured. The company paid a $200,000 fine. In 2005, and 2007 Sara Lee issued recalls for products that may have contained metal fragments, undeclared milk products and potential listeria contamination.  ','http://google2.fda.gov/search?q=sara+lee+inc&x=0&y=0&client=FDAgov&proxystylesheet=FDAgov&output=xml_no_dtd&sort=date%253AD%253AL%253Ad1&site=FDAgov-Recalls-Safety: http://www.knowmore.org/wiki/index.php?title=Ball_Park_Franks_Fiasco:_21_Dead%2C_%24200%2C000_Fine',NULL),(26509,NULL,1135,2750,'No Deviation',NULL,NULL),(26510,NULL,1135,2751,'In May 2002, Sara Lee agreed to pay $3.5 million to 139 black employees who complained of racial harassment and retaliation at Sara Lee subsidiary Hygrade Food Products Corp., a hot-dog plant that closed in 2001. The settlement came after 23 separate racial discrimination suits were filed in June 2001 by African-American employees against the company. The suits, filed in U.S. District Court, alleged that the African-American employees of the Philadelphia Ball Park brand hot dog factory were harassed, subjected to racial epithets, and denied promotions. The suit claimed that white employees received word-of-mouth notice about promotions and transfers.1','http://www.knowmore.org/wiki/index.php?title=Sara_Lee_Agrees_To_Pay_%243.5_Million_To_Black_Employees',NULL),(26508,NULL,1135,2745,'Three Sara Lee salespeople have admitted to wrongly assisting Royal Ahold efforts to falsely inflate revenues by signing confirmation letters that gave inflated rebate numbers.\" (Washington Post, April 8, 2003) ','http://www.knowmore.org/wiki/index.php?title=Sara_Lee_Corp.',NULL),(26505,NULL,1135,2735,'Company information does not indicate a policy for the reduction of energy use',NULL,NULL),(26506,NULL,1135,2739,'Company information does not indicate a policy for the reduction of office waste.',NULL,NULL),(26507,NULL,1135,2742,'Earthgrains Baking Companies, Inc., a subsidiary of Sara Lee, reached a $5.25 million settlement with the Department of Justice and the EPA for committing the \"largest ever corporate-wide violations of stratospheric ozone protection regulations.\" Of the 67 facilities run by Earthgrains, 57 leaked refrigerants at a rate 35% higher than allowed by law. In addition, the company made no attempt to correct leakage problems even after their discovery. Refrigerants such as chlorofluorocarbons (CFCs) are known to be a major cause of ozone layer depletion.\" (U.S. Department of Justice, 07/31/2003) ','http://www.knowmore.org/wiki/index.php?title=Sara_Lee_Corp.',NULL),(26503,NULL,1135,2728,'No information found on company indicating policy on factory energy use.',NULL,NULL),(26504,NULL,1135,2732,'In 2009 A Freedom of Information request to 