orted workplace fatalities/catastrophic incidents or have high rates of lost-time workplace injuries and illnesses since 2000.This company has a 2005 injury rate of 8.18 per 100 employees, which is above the national average (2.4 per 100 employees) for that year. Sara Lee Bakery Group in Phoenix, Arizona has been recognized by The Safety and Health Achievement Recognition Program (SHARP) administered by the Occupational Safety and Health Administration (OSHA). However  Sara Lee Garments, according to workplace medical experts, employees at Sara Lee garment supplier Monclova International in Mexico, are “incapable of doing their work due to the irreversible harm caused by workplace injuries.” In an August 11, 2006 press conference, three women spoke out against worker violations in the textile factory. Workers cited 10 hour workdays, significant decreases in salaries though production levels increased, and the lack of medical assistance as examples of labor violations. Lauro Presqueira, General Manager of Monclova International, stated, “We are confident that all reasonable measures have been identified and implemented” to minimize workplace injuries.\" ',':http://www.workingamerica.org/jobtracker/index.cfm?appState=localSafetyViolation&sortToggle=DESC&zipCode=&companyName=sara%20lee&stateSelect=&zipRadius=100&industry=&start=51http://www.osha.gov/dcsp/smallbusiness/sharp_sites.html#Alabama : http://www.knowmore.org/wiki/index.php?title=Sara_Lee_Corp. :http://www.workingamerica.org/jobtracker/index.cfm?zipCode=&companyName=&industry=&appState=companyDetails&sortToggle=DESC&companyid=2036017',NULL),(26494,NULL,1135,2697,'Company information does not indicate the use of non inorganic fertilizers.','http://www.thejoyofeating.com/products.asp',NULL),(26495,NULL,1135,2700,'Company information does not indicate the use of animal products.',NULL,NULL),(26496,NULL,1135,2705,'Company information does not indicate a Noted Negative Impact of Production, or that  Ingredients are