use for any extended period of time.','http://www.oldorchardjuice.com/sustainability.pdf',NULL),(39514,NULL,1741,3008,'Old Orchard currently employs water conservation methods with its waste water treatment and discharge.  The company discharges only 10,000 gallons per day (GPD), while the beverage industry average is nearly 3 times that amount, based on identical production volume. Additionally, the company\'s physical plant exterior was designed with shade-producing trees and vegetation that eliminates routine watering.\n','/www.oldorchardjuice.com/green/water.htm',NULL),(39515,NULL,1741,3039,'No GMO\'s found in their products.','http://www.oldorchardjuice.com/juice.htm',NULL),(39516,NULL,1741,2978,'In 2006 the company purchased equipment which allows it to recycle corrugated paperboard, plastic stretch wrap, plastic pallet banding, PET and HDPE packaging. The company currently recycles nearly 22 tons of second-generation packaging on a monthly basis, reducing landfill by nearly 250 tons annually.','http://www.oldorchardjuice.com/sustainability.pdf',NULL),(39513,NULL,1741,2991,'Juice manufacturer Old Orchard Brands is expanding its financial support for the Juvenile Diabetes Research Foundation (JDRF). A press release issued by the company announced intentions to give up to one million dollars in new funding. The company hopes to raise money for the JDRF with its Healthy Balance Challenge, in which twenty cents from each sale of Old Orchard Brands Healthy Balance line of low-sugar fruit juices will be donated to the JDRF. The JDRF accepted Old Orchard\'s support last year and, according to Old Orchard, the company has pledged $650,000 worth of cash and product donations through 2009. Money raised through the Healthy Balance Challenge will be in addition to that sum. Arnold Donald, CEO of the JDRF, says partners such as Old Orchard Brands \"care deeply about the work they do in researching a cure for type 1 diabetes. They continue to support their organization with innovative retail-driven programs that increase funding for research, and that\'s a rare and valuable partner to have.\"\n','www.thediabetesblog.com/tag/JDRF/',NULL),(39512,NULL,1741,2971,'In 2006, Old Orchard purchased equipment which allows us to recycle corrugated paperboard, plastic stretch wrap, plastic palleting banding, PET, and  HDPE packaging.  Through this process, we have been able to reduce landfill waste by nearly 250 tons on an annual basis. In 2005, the company was able to reduce the weight of its 64oz PET bottle from 81 grams to 66.5 grams, eliminating nearly 1,000 tons of PET resin.  The industry average is currently around 75 grams.Old Orchard has also successfully reduced the weight of its 12 oz plastic can from 28 grams to 23 grams of HDPE, with a target weight of 21 grams by 2009.  We have been able to save nearly 500,000 pounds of HDPE plastic, while, unfortunately, our competitors continue to use a 28 gram can.\n','www.oldorchard sustainability',NULL),(39506,NULL,1741,2997,'No Deviation',NULL,NULL),(39507,NULL,1741,2984,'No Deviation',NULL,NULL),(39508,NULL,1741,2995,'Nothing found','Nothing Found',NULL),(39509,NULL,1741,2989,'Nothing found on Old Orchard','Nothing Found',NULL),(39510,NULL,1741,2981,'No Deviation','No Deviation',NULL),(39511,NULL,1741,3058,'There  64 oz plastic containers are PET (polyethylene Terephthalate) #1 Plastic. Our 12 oz plastic containers are HDPE (High Density Polyethylene) #2 and the lids of these containers are LLDPE (Linear Low Density Polyethylene) #4. All are recyclable in most recycling stations through-out the country.Progress to date: In 2006 the company purchased equipment which allows it to recycle corrugated paperboard, plastic stretch wrap, plastic pallet banding, PET and HDPE packaging. The company currently recycles nearly 22 tons of second-generation packaging on a monthly basis, reducing landfill by nearly 250 tons annually.','www.oldorchard.com/sustainability',NULL),(39505,NULL,1741,3051,'No Deviation',NULL,NULL),(39525,NULL,1741,3026,'No Deviation',NULL,NULL),(39526,NULL,1741,3047,'No Deviation',NULL,NULL),(39527,NULL,1741,3024,'In July 2001 the firm had a small ammonia leak in its plant, and called the local fire department for assistance, which led to a regional Hazardous Materials Team being mobilized. The city later billed the firm $20,000 for this service, and when Old Orchard protested that the response had been excessive, the city sued. The company later settled by agreeing to pay $15,000.','www.answers.com/topic/old-orchard-brands-llc;www.mlive.com/business/west-michigan/index.ssf/2010/01/investor_group_sues_old_orchar.html',NULL),(39528,NULL,1741,3034,'No Deviation',NULL,NULL),(39529,NULL,1741,3037,'Old Orchard does not support Animal testing and has signed a PETA agreement that it will not fund or support any experiments.','http://www.caringconsumer.com/products_juice.asp',NULL),(39564,NULL,1745,3017,'No Deviation',NULL,NULL),(39565,NULL,1745,3056,'No Deviation',NULL,NULL),(39566,NULL,1745,3029,'No Deviation',NULL,NULL),(39567,NULL,1745,2967,'They use BEF, the Bonneville Environmental Foundation. There mission is to support the development of renewable energy and watershed restoration while empowering people to shrink their carbon footprint.Founded in Portland, Oregon in 1998, BEF is a national, nonprofit organization. One of our proudest achievements to date has been our role in the development of the carbon offset market. In 2000, we helped to create the voluntary market for carbon offsets by closing the first retail REC trade deal with the Environmental Protection Agency. We also launched the first online carbon calculator in 2001. In 2008, our retail Green Tags were renamed BEF Carbon Offsets to meet the naming conventions of the Green-e® Climate program. All of our Carbon Offset products are Green-e® Climate certified, the highest certification possible. With BEF Carbon Offsets, organizations and individuals are able to dedicate funds to the d